snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Dr Mike,
I'm a speech language pathologist. I can better answer the drinking while eating question.


TLDR: Yes, it is recommended you drink while eating to help the swallowing process.


Basically, water hydrates your mouth and you need it to be moist to help chew your food into a ball so it can transport from your mouth, to your esophagus, and to your digestive track. This drinking, then eating a few bits, then taking some more sips of your beverage actually helps push down the food more easily in your esophagus.


I would love to see you pair up with allied health professionals so people can see the whole team working with the patient and their whole body!
